3 DRYWALL tips you’ll want to save! 

1- Seal the BROWN PAPER! WHY?! It will prevent any moisture coming through the drywall. Aswell as primes the paper for mudding!

2. Clean Mud Knives in between each coat!
The tiniest piece of dried mud can create a line through the mud you just added! 

3. Sand & wipe down walls in between coats! 
Sanding ensures smoothness. Wiping with a damp cloth removes extra sanding debris for the next layer to have MAX  adhesion!

Comment below your tip! & follow for more!

1 Thing I should’ve done SOONER when Flipping Furniture! 
Just add wallpaper for a liner! (ad) I am using Rose - Winter Garden by  @photowall_sweden. 

HOW-TO:
- Measure and cut down to size. 
- Secure with adhesive. 
- Apply some pressure to make sure there are no bubbles.
- Trim to make sure it’s perfect!

That’s it, now you have a perfectly levitated Piece!

Pro Tip:
When measuring for trim cuts for the horizontal pieces. Make sure you add the width of the vertical trim and a 1 inch overhang on the horizontal trim. 

EX: (Vertical trim each side X2) 2.5” + (overhang both sides X2)  1” + (window width) 23” = 31” (Overall)
